{
  "page": "Warrior women",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Visenya.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/de/Visenya.jpg/300px-Visenya.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"420\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/de/Visenya.jpg/450px-Visenya.jpg 1.5x, /images/d/de/Visenya.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Visenya.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Visenya_Targaryen\" title=\"Visenya Targaryen\">Visenya Targaryen</a>, who wielded the <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_steel\" title=\"Valyrian steel\">Valyrian steel</a> sword <a href=\"/index.php/Dark_Sister\" title=\"Dark Sister\">Dark Sister</a> - by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://en.amokanet.ru/gallery/martin/\">Amok©</a></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Tizianobaracchibrienneoftarth.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d7/Tizianobaracchibrienneoftarth.jpg/300px-Tizianobaracchibrienneoftarth.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"250\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/d7/Tizianobaracchibrienneoftarth.jpg/450px-Tizianobaracchibrienneoftarth.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/d7/Tizianobaracchibrienneoftarth.jpg/600px-Tizianobaracchibrienneoftarth.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Tizianobaracchibrienneoftarth.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Brienne of Tarth<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> is the only living child and heir of <a href=\"/index.php/Selwyn_Tarth\" title=\"Selwyn Tarth\">Selwyn Tarth</a>, Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Evenfall_Hall\" title=\"Evenfall Hall\">Evenfall</a> and head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarth\" title=\"House Tarth\">House Tarth</a>.</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ygritte_by_steamey.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/97/Ygritte_by_steamey.jpg/300px-Ygritte_by_steamey.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"386\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/97/Ygritte_by_steamey.jpg/450px-Ygritte_by_steamey.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/97/Ygritte_by_steamey.jpg/600px-Ygritte_by_steamey.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ygritte_by_steamey.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Ygritte\" title=\"Ygritte\">Ygritte</a> by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://steamey.deviantart.com\">Steamey©</a>.</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dacy_Mormont.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/8/88/Dacy_Mormont.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"462\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dacy_Mormont.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Dacey_Mormont\" title=\"Dacey Mormont\">Dacey Mormont</a> depiction by Amok©</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Hyrkoon_women_in_Vaes_Dothrak_-_GoT_Histories_%26_Lore_S6.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Hyrkoon_women_in_Vaes_Dothrak_-_GoT_Histories_%26_Lore_S6.png/300px-Hyrkoon_women_in_Vaes_Dothrak_-_GoT_Histories_%26_Lore_S6.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"652\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/8/89/Hyrkoon_women_in_Vaes_Dothrak_-_GoT_Histories_%26_Lore_S6.png 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Hyrkoon_women_in_Vaes_Dothrak_-_GoT_Histories_%26_Lore_S6.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Hyrkoon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hyrkoon\">Hyrkoon</a> warrior maid © HBO</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Warrior women</b> are women who are trained in the arts of warfare and take part in battle, warfare etc.  \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#About\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">About</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Warrior_Women_of_Westeros\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Warrior Women of Westeros</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Warrior_Women_Beyond_the_Wall\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Warrior Women Beyond the Wall</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Warrior_Women_of_Essos\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Warrior Women of Essos</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Warrior_Women_of_the_Summer_Islands\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Warrior Women of the Summer Islands</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"About\">About</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Warrior_women&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: About\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> male warriors are plentiful.  Westerosi warrior women on the other hand are quite uncommon.  Westerosi women however are not forbidden from becoming warriors but neither is it encouraged or seen as acceptable and feminine by many Westerosi.  Nor is a woman viewed as a suitable opponent for men, especially during one-to-one combat. Even hitting <a href=\"/index.php/House_Piper\" title=\"House Piper\">a shield with the image of a woman</a> can make <a href=\"/index.php/Daven_Lannister\" title=\"Daven Lannister\">a man</a> feel unchivalrous.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc33p_606.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc33p_606.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  \n</p><p>Despite Westeros having a martial culture, a culture that reveres the warrior,<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> no separate warrior class in exists for women in Westeros, except in the ranks of the <a href=\"/index.php/Poor_Fellows\" title=\"Poor Fellows\">Poor Fellows</a>, a military order under the command of the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon\" title=\"High Septon\">High Septon</a>. They accepted women as warriors.\n</p><p>One of the few famous warrior women in <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>’s histories is <a href=\"/index.php/Visenya_Targaryen\" title=\"Visenya Targaryen\">Visenya Targaryen</a>, who wielded the <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_steel\" title=\"Valyrian steel\">Valyrian steel</a> sword <a href=\"/index.php/Dark_Sister\" title=\"Dark Sister\">Dark Sister</a> and rode <a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a> into battle.  Unlike her sister <a href=\"/index.php/Visenya_Targaryen\" title=\"Visenya Targaryen\">Visenya Targaryen</a> there is no mention of <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen\">Rhaenys</a> wielding a sword or any other weapon but like her sister she commanded armies and rode <a href=\"/index.php/Meraxes\" title=\"Meraxes\">her dragon</a> into battle during the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_Conquest\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"War of Conquest\">War of Conquest</a>.  According to <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a> both women were warriors and dragonriders in their own rights.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Nymeria\" title=\"Nymeria\">Nymeria</a>, the warrior-queen of the <a href=\"/index.php/Rhoyne\" title=\"Rhoyne\">Rhoyne</a> who conquered Dorne, is well known, however Nymeria was a war leader but not a warrior - that is, a commander rather than a combatant.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> However, other Rhoynish women in history were said to have fought as fiercely as Rhoynish men.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_ancient_history:_ten_thousand_ships.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_ancient_history:_ten_thousand_ships.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In Westeros women tend to be considered the gentler sex, in need of protection.  The ability for a woman to be able to defend herself is considered unnecessary and unfeminine besides.  Highborn women are not encouraged towards warfare or expected to know how to physically defend themselves, although they may perhaps be instructed on the tactics of warfare, especially if they are female heirs to a House.  Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">Randyll Tarly</a> sums up many a man’s thought on women warriors, \n</p>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The gods made men to fight, and women to bear children.  A woman’s war is in the birthing bed.</p></div>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It is not possible for a woman to become a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a>, nor is there a female equivalent of knighthood for a woman who is bent on living a martial life, for a woman who also wishes to abide by a chivalric code.  Although <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne\">Brienne</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Tarth\" title=\"Tarth\">Tarth</a> is as skilled as most any a knight there is no place among them for a woman such as she.   Nor is there a feminine title for a woman warrior, such as <i>Ser</i> as knights have, to acknowledge her ability and chosen vocation, much to the confusion of <a href=\"/index.php/Podrick_Payne\" title=\"Podrick Payne\">Podrick Payne</a>.  \n</p><p>Further <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a> however it is not so unusual for a woman to be able to physically defend herself.  The women of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Mormont\" title=\"House Mormont\">House Mormont</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Bear_Island\" title=\"Bear Island\">Bear Island</a> have had no choice but to learn how to preserve themselves during attacks from <a href=\"/index.php/Ironmen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ironmen\">ironmen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Wildling\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wildling\">wildling</a> raiders while their menfolk are absent.  Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Maege_Mormont\" title=\"Maege Mormont\">Maege Mormont</a> tells <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a>,\n</p>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>We have needed to be [warriors].  In olden days the ironmen would come raiding in their longboats, or wildlings from the <a href=\"/index.php/Frozen_Shore\" title=\"Frozen Shore\">Frozen Shore</a>.  The men would be off fishing, like as not.  The wives they left behind had to defend themselves and their children, or else be carried off.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos45p_522.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos45p_522.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div>\n</blockquote> \n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">Beyond the Wall</a> there are <a href=\"/index.php/Spearwife\" title=\"Spearwife\">spearwives</a>, they are accepted and respected by the men of the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Folk\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Free Folk\">Free Folk</a>.  The Free Folk culture is a warrior culture, one that gives women the right, but not the obligation, to be fighters. <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> The same applies to the mountain clansmen of the <a href=\"/index.php/Mountains_of_the_Moon\" title=\"Mountains of the Moon\">Mountains of the Moon</a>, who are also a First Men tribal culture, like the Free Folk; <a href=\"/index.php/Chella\" title=\"Chella\">Chella</a>, daughter of Cheyk, is a woman warchief of her own clan.\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> are more also more accepting of women warriors and are willing to fight alongside them.  \n</p><p>Some of the women of <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a> fight but it's not the rule.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Islands\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Summer Islands\">Summer Islands</a> have warrior woman, once such warrior woman was <a href=\"/index.php/Xanda_Qo\" title=\"Xanda Qo\">Xanda Qo</a>, Princess of Sweet Lotus Vale, who united all of the islands under her rule.\n</p><p>Amongst the <a href=\"/index.php/Jogos_Nhai\" title=\"Jogos Nhai\">Jogos Nhai</a> There are also female <i><a href=\"/index.php/Jhat\" title=\"Jhat\">jhats</a></i> but girls who choose the warrior's way are expected to dress and live as men.\n</p><p>In the ancient nation of the <a href=\"/index.php/Patrimony_of_Hyrkoon\" title=\"Patrimony of Hyrkoon\">Patrimony of Hyrkoon</a> there was possibly a custom of having warrior women.  A present there is a culture for warrior woman east of the <a href=\"/index.php/Bone_Mountains\" title=\"Bone Mountains\">Bone Mountains</a> which may originate from the Patrimony.  There are warrior maids of <a href=\"/index.php/Kayakayanaya\" title=\"Kayakayanaya\">Kayakayanaya</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Bayasabhad\" title=\"Bayasabhad\">Bayasabhad</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Shamyriana\" title=\"Shamyriana\">Shamyriana</a> who fight bare-breasted and pierce their nipples with iron rings and cheeks with rubies. <a href=\"/index.php/Lomas_Longstrider\" title=\"Lomas Longstrider\">Lomas Longstrider</a> apparently visited these successor cities as he said that there are no fiercer fighters in the world than their warrior women.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_bones_and_beyond.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_bones_and_beyond.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>The greatest of the <a href=\"/index.php/Sarnori\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sarnori\">Sarnori</a> went to battle in scythed <a href=\"/index.php/Chariot\" title=\"Chariot\">chariots</a> pulled by teams of bloodred horses. These were often driven by their wives or daughters, for it was the custom among the Tall Men for men and women to make war together.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_grasslands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_grasslands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>It is not known if the <a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyrians</a> had warrior women.  Thus far there has been no mention of <a href=\"/index.php/Dark_Sister\" title=\"Dark Sister\">Dark Sister</a> being passed on to a female <a href=\"/index.php/Targaryen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Targaryen\">Targaryen</a> after Visenya. There is, however, ample evidence for the existence of female dragonlords both in ancient Valyria and among the Targaryens.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Warrior_Women_of_Westeros\">Warrior Women of Westeros</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Warrior_women&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Warrior Women of Westeros\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:102px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Needle,_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/4c/Needle%2C_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg/100px-Needle%2C_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg\" width=\"100\" height=\"385\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/4c/Needle%2C_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg/150px-Needle%2C_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg 1.5x, /images/4/4c/Needle%2C_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Needle,_Sword_of_Arya_Stark.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Needle\" title=\"Needle\">Needle</a></div></div></div>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Visenya_Targaryen\" title=\"Visenya Targaryen\">Visenya Targaryen</a> – famously wielded <a href=\"/index.php/Dark_Sister\" title=\"Dark Sister\">Dark Sister</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a> – wields <a href=\"/index.php/Oathkeeper\" title=\"Oathkeeper\">Oathkeeper</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Asha_Greyjoy\" title=\"Asha Greyjoy\">Asha Greyjoy</a> – fights with two throwing axes in either hand</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> – wields <a href=\"/index.php/Needle\" title=\"Needle\">Needle</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Meera_Reed\" title=\"Meera Reed\">Meera Reed</a> – fights with a net and spear</li>\n<li>The women of <a href=\"/index.php/Bear_Island\" title=\"Bear Island\">Bear Island</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Hagen%27s_beautiful_red-haired_daughter\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hagen&#39;s beautiful red-haired daughter\">Hagen's beautiful red-haired daughter</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Obara_Sand\" title=\"Obara Sand\">Obara Sand</a> - wields a spear and whip.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Chella\" title=\"Chella\">Chella</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Meris\" title=\"Meris\">Meris</a> - <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsword\">sellsword</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Windblown\" title=\"Windblown\">Windblown</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Wenda_the_White_Fawn\" title=\"Wenda the White Fawn\">Wenda the White Fawn</a> - <a href=\"/index.php/Outlaw\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Outlaw\">outlaw</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingswood_Brotherhood\" title=\"Kingswood Brotherhood\">Kingswood Brotherhood</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Meg\" title=\"Meg\">Swampy Meg</a> - a member of the <a href=\"/index.php/Brotherhood_without_Banners\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brotherhood without Banners\">Brotherhood without Banners</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Danelle_Lothston\" title=\"Danelle Lothston\">Danelle Lothston</a> - the \"Mad Lady\" of Harrenhal, who personally commanded her men-at-arms and wore armor during the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"Second Blackfyre Rebellion\">Second Blackfyre Rebellion</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Wylla_of_Wyl\" title=\"Wylla of Wyl\">Wylla of Wyl</a> - shieldmaiden</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Agnes_Blackwood\" title=\"Agnes Blackwood\">Agnes Blackwood</a> - Lady of Raventree Hall, marched on by the <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Century_of_Blood\" title=\"Century of Blood\">Century of Blood</a></li>\n<li>Poxy <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Poore\" title=\"Jeyne Poore\">Jeyne Poore</a> - A captain of the <a href=\"/index.php/Poor_Fellows\" title=\"Poor Fellows\">Poor Fellows</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_Militant_uprising\" title=\"Faith Militant uprising\">Faith Militant uprising</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Melony_Piper\" title=\"Melony Piper\">Melony Piper</a> - donned man's mail and a spear in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_Beneath_the_Gods_Eye\" title=\"Battle Beneath the Gods Eye\">Battle Beneath the Gods Eye</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Jonquil_Darke\" title=\"Jonquil Darke\">Jonquil Darke</a> - <a href=\"/index.php/Sworn_shield\" title=\"Sworn shield\">sworn shield</a> to Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alysanne_Targaryen\" title=\"Alysanne Targaryen\">Alysanne Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Sabitha_Frey\" title=\"Sabitha Frey\">Sabitha Frey</a> - wore mail and fought in the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Alysanne_Blackwood\" title=\"Alysanne Blackwood\">Alysanne Blackwood</a> - archer for the <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">Blacks</a> during the Dance of the Dragons</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Warrior_Women_Beyond_the_Wall\">Warrior Women Beyond the Wall</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Warrior_women&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Warrior Women Beyond the Wall\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Ygritte\" title=\"Ygritte\">Ygritte</a> - <a href=\"/index.php/Spearwife\" title=\"Spearwife\">spearwife</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Osha\" title=\"Osha\">Osha</a> - spearwife</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Harma_Dogshead\" title=\"Harma Dogshead\">Harma Dogshead</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Ragwyle\" title=\"Ragwyle\">Ragwyle</a> - spearwife</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Hali\" title=\"Hali\">Hali</a> - spearwife</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Val\" title=\"Val\">Val</a> - spearwife</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Holly\" title=\"Holly\">Holly</a> - spearwife</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Rowan\" title=\"Rowan\">Rowan</a> - spearwife</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Squirrel\" title=\"Squirrel\">Squirrel</a> - spearwife</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Frenya\" title=\"Frenya\">Frenya</a> - spearwife</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Myrtle\" title=\"Myrtle\">Myrtle</a> - spearwife</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Willow_Witch-eye\" title=\"Willow Witch-eye\">Willow Witch-eye</a>  - spearwife</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Harma\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Harma\">Harma</a> - spearwife</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Munda\" title=\"Munda\">Munda</a> - spearwife</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Thistle\" title=\"Thistle\">Thistle</a> - spearwife</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Black_Maris\" title=\"Black Maris\">Black Maris</a> - spearwife</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Warrior_Women_of_Essos\">Warrior Women of Essos</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Warrior_women&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Warrior Women of Essos\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Penny\" title=\"Penny\">Penny</a>, a dwarf woman, attached to <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Sons\" title=\"Second Sons\">Second Sons</a>, armors herself for the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_siege_of_Meereen\" title=\"Second siege of Meereen\">second siege of Meereen</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Barsena\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Barsena\">Barsena</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Pit_fighters\" title=\"Pit fighters\">pit-fighter</a>, who had slain every other woman sent against her.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Malazza\" title=\"Malazza\">Malazza</a>, the Girl General, a <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a>'i noblewoman and commander of the <a href=\"/index.php/Wise_Masters\" title=\"Wise Masters\">Wise Masters</a>.</li>\n<li>warrior maids of <a href=\"/index.php/Bayasabhad\" title=\"Bayasabhad\">Bayasabhad</a></li>\n<li>warrior maids of <a href=\"/index.php/Shamyriana\" title=\"Shamyriana\">Shamyriana</a></li>\n<li>warrior maids of <a href=\"/index.php/Kayakayanaya\" title=\"Kayakayanaya\">Kayakayanaya</a></li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Jhattar\" title=\"Jhattar\">jhattar</a></i> <a href=\"/index.php/Zhea\" title=\"Zhea\">Zhea</a></li>\n<li>some <a href=\"/index.php/Jhat\" title=\"Jhat\">jhats</a> and jhattars of the <a href=\"/index.php/Jogos_Nhai\" title=\"Jogos Nhai\">Jogos Nhai</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Kingdom_of_Sarnor\" title=\"Kingdom of Sarnor\">Sarnori</a> warrior women</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Warrior_Women_of_the_Summer_Islands\">Warrior Women of the Summer Islands</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Warrior_women&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Warrior Women of the Summer Islands\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Kojja_Mo\" title=\"Kojja Mo\">Kojja Mo</a>, an expert marksman</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Xanda_Qo\" title=\"Xanda Qo\">Xanda Qo</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Chatana_Qo\" title=\"Chatana Qo\">Chatana Qo</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Warrior_women&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>All men must die, and women too... but not all will be remembered.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Barsena\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Barsena\">Barsena</a> to Daenerys <a href=\"/index.php/Targaryen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Targaryen\">Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>It is a rare and precious gift to be a knight.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Men will always underestimate you and their pride will make them want to vanquish you quickly, lest it be said that a woman tried them sorely.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Goodwin\" title=\"Goodwin\">Goodwin</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Ser? <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne\">My Lady</a>?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Podrick_Payne\" title=\"Podrick Payne\">Podrick Payne</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Her last foe <a href=\"/index.php/Morgan_Liddle\" title=\"Morgan Liddle\">was a northman with an axe</a>, a big man bald and bearded, clad in a byrnie of patched and rusted mail that could only mean he was a chief or champion. He was not pleased to find himself fighting a woman.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Asha_Greyjoy\" title=\"Asha Greyjoy\">Asha Greyjoy</a>'s thoughts</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>What <a href=\"/index.php/House_Mormont\" title=\"House Mormont\">we</a> are is what <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">you</a> made us. On <a href=\"/index.php/Bear_Island\" title=\"Bear Island\">Bear Island</a> every child learns to fear the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Greyjoy\" title=\"House Greyjoy\">krakens</a> rising from the sea.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Alysane_Mormont\" title=\"Alysane Mormont\">Alysane Mormont</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Asha_Greyjoy\" title=\"Asha Greyjoy\">Asha Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Her very womanhood seemed to offend <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">him</a>. Men from the <a href=\"/index.php/Green_lands\" title=\"Green lands\">green lands</a> liked their women soft and sweet in silk, she knew, not clad in mail and leather with a throwing axe in each hand.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Asha_Greyjoy\" title=\"Asha Greyjoy\">Asha Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p> I wanted to present my female characters in great diversity, even in a society as sexist and patriarchal as the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>. Women would find different roles and different personalities, so women with different talents would find ways to work with it in a society according to who they are. <sup id=\"cite_ref-20\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-20\">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>She is supposed to be freakish.  She was an answer to the bad fantasy cliché of warrior women.<sup id=\"cite_ref-21\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-21\">&#91;21&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>, on <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Warrior_women&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_22\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 22\">Chapter 22</a>, Catelyn II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc33p_606.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7